<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="576" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,762,1723]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,870,895]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is unique in external appearance due to the indistinct forewing orbicular and reniform stigmata, the dentate submarginal line rather than straight in other species of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wileman &amp; West" baseAuthorityYear="1929" box="[1078,1190,907,931]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hoplodrina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="implacata">
<emphasis box="[1078,1190,907,931]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="576">implacata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group. In the male genitalia, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wu &amp; Owada" authorityYear="2018" box="[325,450,942,966]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hoplodrina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscura">
<emphasis box="[325,450,942,966]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="576">H. obscura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wu &amp; Owada" authorityYear="2018" box="[659,797,943,966]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hoplodrina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cienensis">
<emphasis box="[659,797,943,966]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="576">H. cienensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be separated by the stouter uncus (as that of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wileman &amp; West" baseAuthorityYear="1929" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hoplodrina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="implacata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="576">H. implacata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) rather than slender; the slightly concave ventral margin of valva rather than valva gradually widen towards subapical part; the absence of conical spine on carina rather than the presence of two small conical spines.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="576" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,762,1723]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1050,1075]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576">Description.</emphasis>
Adult (
<figureCitation box="[432,530,1050,1075]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–15" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1777,1800]" captionTargetBox="[246,1325,564,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[246,1343,564,1768]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–15. Habitus of species of Hoplodrina implacata group. 1. H. implacata (Wileman &amp; West, 1929), female, holotype, Taiwan (©The Trustees of the Natural History Museum, London); 2. Ditto, labels (©The Trustees of the Natural History Museum, London); 3, 6. H. implacata, male, Taiwan; 4. H. cienensis sp. nov., male, holotype, Taiwan (TFRI); 5. Ditto, paratype, female, Taiwan (TFRI); 7. H. obscura sp. nov., male, holotype, Taiwan (TFRI); 8. Ditto, paratype, male, Taiwan (TFRI); 9. H. minimalis Kononenko, 1997, male, China (NSMT); 10. H. kononenkoi sp. nov., male, holotype, Taiwan (TFRI); 11. Ditto, paratype, female, Taiwan (TFRI); 12. H. euryptera Boursin, 1937, male, Japan (NSMT); 13. H. bunun sp. nov., male, holotype, Taiwan (NMNS); 14. Ditto, male, paratype, Taiwan (NSMT); 15. Ditto, paratype, female, Taiwan (NSMT). Scale bar= 10 mm. Photo by Shen-Horn Yen (1, 2); Shipher Wu (3–15)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457395/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="576">Figs 7, 8</figureCitation>
)—Forewing length 
<quantity box="[764,844,1051,1075]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="5" pageNumber="576" unit="mm" value="14.0">14 mm</quantity>
in males (n= 2). Antenna filiform in male, ciliate in female. Head and thorax covered with ochreous-grey. Forewing ground color grey. Forewing antemedial line dark grey, strong wave-like, medial part tinged with dark grey band, postmedial line dark grey, moderately serrate; orbicular and reniform stigmata indistinct; submarginal line pale ochreous, dentate; cilia and region between submarginal line and outer margin ochreous-grey; outer margin with small triangular dot locating at central part between each vein; marginal line pale ochreous. Hindwing pale ochreous-grey, gradually darken from two third part from base, discal spot dark grey; marginal line pale ochrous; cilia ochreous-grey. Abdomen ochreous-grey.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,762,1723]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[389,474,1302,1327]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–23" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1712,1735]" captionTargetBox="[293,1283,512,1674]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[290,1296,481,1691]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 16–23. The male genitalia of the genus Hoplodrina species. 16. H. implacata (Wileman &amp; West, 1929), Taiwan (NSMT); 17. H. cienensis sp. nov., paratype, Taiwan (TFRI); 18. H. obscura sp. nov., paratype, Taiwan (TFRI); 19. H. kononenkoi sp. nov., paratype, Taiwan (TFRI); 20. H. bunun sp. nov., paratype, Taiwan (NMNS); 21. H. persequora Ronkay, Ronkay, Fu &amp; Wu, 2013, Taiwan (TFRI); 22. H. minimalis Kononenko, 1997, China (NSMT); 23. H. euryptera Boursin, 1937, Japan (NSMT). Photo by Shipher Wu." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457397/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="576">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
)—Uncus stout, curved toward anterior part, apical part swollen with acute tip. Tegumen moderate in width, peniculus well developed covered with long hair-like scales. Saccus tapered, Vshaped. Valva with costal and ventral margin nearly parallel, medial part of ventral margin slightly excurved; succulus moderate in size, harpe digitiform, straight; corona represented by 6 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1050,1064,1410,1435]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576">–</emphasis>
7 spines. Juxta plate-like, apical margin rounded. Aedeagus about 4/5 length of valva. Carina with three sclerotized bands with ventral part swollen. Vesica with three diverticula, basal one and distal one membranous, medial one covered with short dense spines. Tubular extension of vesica pointing anteriorly when fully swollen. Phallobase protruded anteriorly.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="576" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,762,1723]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,538,1554,1579]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576">Distribution and bionomics.</emphasis>
Endemic to 
<collectingCountry box="[688,774,1554,1579]" name="Taiwan" pageId="5" pageNumber="576">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
. This species is distributed in mid-elevation broad-leaved forests of central north 
<collectingCountry box="[414,500,1590,1615]" name="Taiwan" pageId="5" pageNumber="576">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
. The adults were only collected in late September in Guanwu (
<typeStatus box="[1209,1259,1591,1615]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576">type</typeStatus>
locality) where the whole year fundamental survey was conducted by the first author during 
<date box="[1011,1179,1626,1651]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576" value="2010" valueMax="2011">2010 and 2011</date>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="576" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,762,1723]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1662,1687]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576">Etymology.</emphasis>
Name according to the indistinct forewing maculation that is unique in the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wileman &amp; West" baseAuthorityYear="1929" box="[1186,1436,1662,1686]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hoplodrina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="implacata">
<emphasis box="[1186,1436,1662,1686]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="576">Hoplodrina implacata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
